From Abel Leonard, Lafia Please enable JavaScript This is a modal window. Beginning of dialog window. Escape will cancel and close the window. End of dialog window. Following the poor performance of Nasarawa United football team in the ongoing Nigeria Professional football league 2022/2023 season, chairman of the club, Mr. Isaac Danladi could be shown the exit door as the state ministry of youth and sports development are already making plans for a replacement. Recall that the ministry of youth and sports development headed by Mr. Isaac Lucky Yargwa had handed the team management a three match ultimatum to savage their job. The three matches giving to them was against Gombe united, plateau United and Shooting stars of Ibadan which they were able to gather only one point siting bottom at the NPFL abridged league table in group A. Also Recall that the team had played six NPFL matches Lossing five and drawing against Gonbe United away from their adopted home Kaduna state. According to sources, the state government is not happy with the situation hence the need to change the management of the team and some notable names have been penciled down for the job.